There are several provisions in Ethiopian law to regulate online privacy. For example, the Computer Crime Proclamation No. 958/2016 criminalizes the unauthorized access to, and illegal interception and damage of, computer data.&nbsp;
The Proclamation further prohibits the use of computer systems to disseminate advertisements absent addressee consent.
The new Media Proclamation obliges online Media to protect the data of users and obtain explicit consent from users when circumstances requiring usersâ€™ data to be made available to third parties.Last modified 20 Dec 2021
				
			